    "id": 66,
    "text": "Annex B — Fee Structure for National and International Students. National Student Fee Structure (in PKR): Admission Processing Fee (non-refundable): Rs 35,000 for all programmes. Security Deposit (refundable): Rs 10,000. Tuition Fee per Semester: Engineering/IT, Applied BioSciences, Natural Sciences, Architecture, Industrial Design — Rs 171,350; Business Studies and Social Sciences — Rs 250,380. Grade Improvement Fee (Fall/Spring, per CH): Rs 8,000. Course Registration Fee for Summer Semester (per CH): Rs 8,000. Make-up Fee for Missed OHT/MSE/ESE (per course): Rs 5,000. Miscellaneous Fee: Rs 2,700/semester. Special Note: Harvard Business School licensing fee of Rs 12,000/year is charged to BBA, BS Accounting & Finance, and BS Tourism & Hospitality Management students. International Student Fee Structure (in USD): Admission Processing Fee: USD 600. Tuition Fee per annum: USD 5,400 for all programmes (Engineering, IT, Biosciences, Natural Sciences, Architecture, Business Studies, Social Sciences). Security Deposit (refundable): USD 250. Health Facilities per annum: USD 120. Grade Improvement Fee per CH: USD 40. Summer Semester Course Registration Fee per CH: USD 40. Make-up Fee per course: USD 40. Harvard Business School licensing fee: USD 40/year for BBA, BS Accounting & Finance, and BS Tourism students. Payment Notes: At admission, students pay admission processing fee, security deposit, and full first semester fee. Tuition fee is payable on a semester basis and must be paid before semester commencement. International students pay on annual basis in advance. All students are responsible for keeping copies of paid invoices throughout their academic tenure. All fees and charges are subject to revision from time to time.",
